## (1)(a) IEEE Function and Standards

> Explain the functions of the IEEE (Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers) and give two of its standards. *(4 marks)*

---

The **IEEE** is a professional organization that develops **technical standards** for electrical, electronic, and computing technologies.

**Functions:**
- Creates standards for networking, hardware, and communications
- Develops the **802** family of LAN/MAN standards
- Publishes technical papers and educational resources

**Two IEEE Standards:**

| Standard | Name | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| **IEEE 802.11** | WiFi | Wireless LAN |
| **IEEE 802.16** | WiMAX | Wireless Metropolitan Area Network |

